title: For Trade:  Requesting Information on Taurus M605 Protector Poly 357
postcontent:
Hey Armslist Surfers...I recently bought a Taurus M605 Protector Poly 357 (used) and have the following problems that I am looking for some information on.  I know it is BUYER BEWARE when buying used firearms, however, I have always had safe experiences using Armslist (until now, that is.)

I cycled the gun and gave it a good once over before buying.  Didn't even shoot it for five days.  Today I put 25 rounds of 357 through it, then it stopped cycling.  I could not cock the hammer for single action fire, nor would it fire in double action.  I unloaded it, checked it over, still nothing.  Came inside to call Taurus, and thanks to their excessive hold time I started working the gun again.  It started cycling correctly, so I hung up on Taurus after 20 minutes on hold and went outside to shoot it again.

This time I put 20 rounds of 38 Special through it before it started the same thing again.  Yes, I have checked and double checked the "safety lock" on the back of the hammer.  Yes, the gun is clean.  It seems to me, and I know it sounds crazy, but when the gun gets hot it stops working.  After it cools, it works again.

Any assistance would be greatly appreciated.  I have called Taurus a total of three times, each time being on hold for over 20 minutes.  I have decided instead to send the president of the company a personal letter.  I am retired Navy and very patient so I no rush on this.  I just want my gun to work properly--what's the purpose of having a self-defense gun that does not work 100 percent every single time?  I also buy two of all handguns I am interested in, at least I have in the past, but now I am wary of the Taurus brand and fear I am stuck with a lemon.  Even with their supposedly fantastic warranty, I am not the original owner and they can always "find" some sort of user-induced problem.

title: For Sale:  Finnish M28 Mosin Nagant - 7.62X54R
postcontent:
For sale is a Finnish Mosin Nagant. It is the M28 model which is the same model used by the most effective sniper in world history Simo Hayha,with about 700 kills in 100 days. This is a genuine piece of history, and also an excellent shooting rifle.

For those who dont know, The Finnish Army took the Mosin Nagant and rebuilt it into a truly effective bolt action rifle.This particular one is a Tikka.

This gun is in great shape with a good bore. It will be at home on the range and the mantle. It is a Civil Guard (White Guard) Rifle and can be traced via serial number to the very unit it was originally issued. Pretty neat peice of history to say the least.

Pics of uch a long gun are impractical and hence not included in the add. If you look it up online you will know what the M28 Mosin Nagant is. You will also find it is one of the more rare models and as such this will probably be the only chance to get one.
